-- GV Gold London IPO May Value Russian Company at $791 Million, Mail Reports
-- B y   L a r s   P a u l s s o n
-- 2010-09-26T10:10:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-26/gv-gold-london-ipo-may-value-russian-company-at-791-million-mail-reports.html
GV Gold OAO plans a London Stock
Exchange listing that may value the company at as much as 500
million pounds ($791 million) the  Mail on Sunday  reported
without saying where it got the information.  GV Gold, which is based in Bodaibo, Russia, hired Credit
Suisse Group in 2007 as an adviser for a 200 million-pound
listing which was later abandoned, the paper said. The bank
declined to comment on whether it had been retained, while GV
Gold could not be reached for comment on the reported share
sale, the paper said.  The price of gold reached a record high of $1,301.60 an
ounce on Sept. 24.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Lars Paulsson  in London at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss on   sev@bloomberg.net  